main event: Radar detection of an unidentified object over Djakarta, Indonesia on September 25, 1963.
interesting points: The object was detected by radar, pointing in a specific direction, and while being observed, a piece fell off the main body.
The object got dimmer as it crossed the sky and fell into the ocean when last observed.
The object was visible for 3-4 seconds at an elevation of 45°-50° at night.
The radar return could have indicated either a meteor or a possible missile attempt.
The witness was the son of a local FAA/AID representative, a sophomore engineering student at Ohio State University, and a member of the Air Force ROTC.
photographs: no, the report does not include any photographs
